{"type":"message","id":"231d714f","parentId":"ccbcf69b","timestamp":"2026-03-23T23:38:26.625Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The process was started without command-line arguments visible. Quick tunnels are started with `cloudflared tunnel --url http://localhost:...`. Since I can't get the URL from a running process without its output, and cloudflared is running, let me try a different approach.\n\nI know the webhook URL is empty (confirmed by getWebhookInfo). The cloudflared quick tunnel URL needs to be found or regenerated.\n\nLet me try to:\n1. Kill the existing cloudflared process\n2. Start a new quick tunnel and capture the URL\n3. Set the webhook with the new URL\n\nActually, let me think about this differently. The session `keen-lobster` was mentioned in TOOLS.md as containing the cloudflared URL. \n\nBut the sessions list came back empty. I could restart cloudflared and pipe its output to a file so I can capture the URL that way.","thinkingSignature":"ccb9251d2d4a109e286ebb9ad0fcc9f70707d9ef740b815a5d98e5ebf3f24376"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_jpdp72ryx99a_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# Kill the existing cloudflared process (PID 1904)\nStop-Process -Id 1904 -Force -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue\nStart-Sleep -Seconds 2\n# Start cloudflared quick tunnel and capture URL to a temp file\n$tempUrlFile = \"$env:TEMP\\cf_url.txt\"\n$proc = Start-Process \"C:\\Program Files (x86)\\cloudflared\\cloudflared.exe\" -ArgumentList \"tunnel\",\"--url\",\"http://localhost:8080\" -NoNewWindow -PassThru -RedirectStandardOutput $tempUrlFile\nStart-Sleep -Seconds 8\nif (Test-Path $tempUrlFile) {\n    Get-Content $tempUrlFile\n} else {\n    \"No output file found\"\n}","timeout":20}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":1901,"output":382,"cacheRead":9991,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":12274,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},